@using ProjectFirma.Web.Models
@using LtInfo.Common.HtmlHelperExtensions
@using LtInfo.Common.ModalDialog
@using ProjectFirma.Web.Common
@inherits ProjectFirma.Web.Views.ProjectUpdate.Instructions

@section JavascriptAndStylesContent
{
    <style type="text/css">
        .iconDefinition {
            width: 40px;
            text-align: center;
            display: inline-block;
        }

        li.iconRow {
            margin-left: 20px;
            padding: 4px 4px 4px 0;
        }

        .instructionList li
        {
            padding: 2px 2px 2px 0;
        }
    </style>
}

<p >This @FieldDefinition.Project.GetFieldDefinitionLabel() Update wizard is used to submit annual project updates. All projects in the Planning/Design, Implementation, or Post-Implementation stage are required to submit annual updates. @Html.LinkWithFieldDefinitionFor(FieldDefinition.ProjectStage, String.Format("View {0} Definitions", FieldDefinition.ProjectStage.GetFieldDefinitionLabel()), LabelWithSugarForExtensions.DefaultPopupWidth, new List<string> {"fieldDefinitionLink"})</p>

<p>The various aspects of a project that are available for update can be seen on the left. Several of these sections are optional, but others are required:</p>
<ul class="instructionList">
    <li><strong>Basics:</strong> <i>You must enter the project's start and completion dates</i></li>
    <li><strong>Location - Simple:</strong> <i>You must input your project's location via an interactive map or provide a short location description </i></li>
    <li><strong>@MultiTenantHelpers.GetPerformanceMeasureNamePluralized():</strong> <i>You must enter an accomplishment value for at least one @MultiTenantHelpers.GetPerformanceMeasureName()per year (or indicate you have no accomplishments)</i></li>
    <li><strong>Expenditures:</strong> <i>You must enter at least one Expenditure per year (if you spent nothing, enter a $0 expenditure)</i></li>
    <li><strong>Budgets:</strong> <i>You must enter @FieldDefinition.FundingSource.GetFieldDefinitionLabelPluralized() and project budgets</i></li>
</ul>
<p>In order to submit an update, all required information must be provided. You will see some icons next to some pages – here is what they mean:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: none; padding: 0">
    <li class="iconRow">
        <div class="iconDefinition">@Html.Raw(ProjectWizardComponents.RequiredInfoNotProvidedIcon)</div> Required information has not been completely provided (you can't submit this update)
    </li>
    <li class="iconRow">
        <div class="iconDefinition">@Html.Raw(ProjectWizardComponents.SectionHasUpdatesIcon)</div> This section has been updated - Use the "Show Changes" button to see changes
    </li>
</ul>

<p>Submitting this update will notify the reviewer. Your updates will be approved or returned to you for corrections/clarifications. The official project record will not be modified until the update is approved.</p>
<p>Click the <span class="helpicon glyphicon glyphicon-question-sign blue" title="Help"></span> icon to view field-specific help, and to see the reporting guidance for a specific @MultiTenantHelpers.GetPerformanceMeasureName(). You can also see this same guidance on the Detail pages available from the list of  <a href="@ViewDataTyped.PerformanceMeasuresUrl" target="_blank">@MultiTenantHelpers.GetPerformanceMeasureNamePluralized()</a>.
</p>
<p>
    If you have questions or run into problems, please @(ModalDialogFormHelper.ModalDialogFormLink("Request Support", ViewDataTyped.RequestSupportUrl, "request support", 800, "Submit Request", "Cancel", new List<string>(), null, null)).
</p>
@using (Html.BeginForm())
{
    <div class="text-right">
        <button class="btn btn-xs btn-firma" type="submit" style="margin-left: 10px">Begin Update</button>
    </div>
}
